{
  "texts": [
    "The phased introduction aims to focus initial oversight on very large entities with the most influence, before expanding coverage.",
    "However, smaller platforms have warned of significant compliance burdens, and in February 2024 Coordinators figures were yet not fully operational [121,123].As a final note, continued assessment during roll-out was a strategic preparation to ensure proportionality across diverse intermediaries.",
    "Indeed, even before the DSA's formal roll-out deadlines platforms and private consultancy firms begun internal implementation efforts as revealed by published readiness checklists outlining provisions [173], alongside the institution of distinct reporting flows for locally illegal content under Article 14's notice-and-action provisions.",
    "For instance, YouTube and Pinterest provided feature customized complaint forms and handling by legal teams [116] before phase-in dates.",
    "Appendix 3: Methodological appraisalCoding DSA critiques categorization in Sect. 3The categorization and analysis of critiques in Sect."
  ]
}